rcing platform. As of 18 Jul 2025 the buyer had not decided whether to keep Coupa and said the RFP is 'not to challenge Coupa'. The strongest CURRENT threat is inertia / do-nothing: the project is on hold as of 8 Jun 2026 with the RFP slipped to March 2027. Deloitte is a live SI influence pushing an S2P+CLM agenda with a stated Coupa bias amid confirmed internal politics. No other named vendor is in evidence.", "competitors": [{"date": "2026-06-08", "name": "Do Nothing / re-optimise Coupa sourcing", "quote": "When the project will be continued I will contact you", "source": "SF Task 08 Jun 2026 (Zsofia Ambrus-Csetreki); Avoma call 18 Jul 2025", "status": "do_nothing", "sentiment": "negative", "how_we_win": "Quantify the cost of 250 manual sourcing events per year and manual scoring so inertia becomes the expensive option, and anchor a compelling event tied to the March 2027 RFP.", "threat_level": "high"}, {"date": "2025-07-18", "name": "Coupa", "quote": "we are not utilizing Coupa for sourcing at all ... we did not put enough energy into the configuration customization", "source": "Avoma discovery call 18 Jul 2025 (Zsofia Ambrus-Csetreki); SF Next_Step__c ('bias towards Coupa')", "status": "incumbent", "sentiment": "neutral", "how_we_win": "Position one integrated sourcing platform that embeds into or dovetails with Coupa reporting and the intake form; show automated scoring and Merlin autonomous negotiation Coupa's under-configured sourcing cannot deliver.", "threat_level": "medium"}, {"date": "2026-05-18", "name": "Deloitte (SI, S2P+CLM agenda)", "quote": "Deloitte has early engagement and pushing for s2p+clm and remove SAP. Bias towards Coupa. Deloitte confirmed internal politics but engaged and will work with us.", "source": "SF Next_Step__c", "status": "active", "sentiment": "negative", "how_we_win": "Engage the head of procurement directly to understand Deloitte's mandate and present a unified S2P + sourcing story that does not require Coupa-centricity.", "threat_level": "medium"}]}, "champion_strength": {"source": "Avoma discovery call 18 Jul 2025; SF Task 08 Jun 2026", "at_risk": true, "summary": "Zsofia Ambrus-Csetreki is engaged and knowledgeable but mid-level and IBM-contracted; she has not delivered the promised demo dates or escalated to the head of procurement, and on 8 Jun 2026 she put the project on hold, so her advocacy is real but stalled and unproven at the executive level.", "champion": "Zsofia Ambrus-Csetreki", "strength": "developing"}, "stakeholder_map": {"items": [{"name": "Zs\u00f3fia Ambrus-Csetreki", "risk": "Mid-level single point of contact with no budget authority; has not delivered demo dates or escalated to power in ~11.7 months.", "role": "Champion", "email": "zsofia.ambrus.csetreki.ext@honda-eu.com", "title": "Sourcing Lead (IT Category)", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "Positive but cooling (enthusiastic on 18 Jul 2025 call, but put the project on hold on 8 Jun 2026)", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2026-06-08"}]}, "meddpicc": {"metrics": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Avoma discovery call 18 Jul 2025 (Zsofia Ambrus-Csetreki)"], "narrative": "The buyer articulated clear qualitative pain but quantified almost nothing. On 18 Jul 2025 Zsofia Ambrus-Csetreki said the team runs approximately 250 sourcing events per year and handles them 'in an old school way', releasing RFPs by email, collecting proposals on SharePoint, and scoring live in meetings on a complex Excel scorecard. The one scope figure she gave is that only indirect sourcing requests above 100k pounds reach her team. No cycle-time, headcount, error-rate, or savings number was ever stated, and on budget she said 'we have a project, but we do not know what to expect'. Converting the 250-events-per-year volume and the manual-scoring effort into a quantified efficiency and ROI case is the open move."}, "champion": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Avoma discovery call 18 Jul 2025 (Zsofia Ambrus-Csetreki)", "SF Task 08 Jun 2026", "SF LastActivityDate 8 Jun 2026"], "narrative": "Zsofia Ambrus-Csetreki is an engaged, knowledgeable working-level contact and the de facto champion: she ran the discovery, has a clear requirements picture, said she wanted to bring the head of procurement into a demo, and was the source of the 8 Jun 2026 email that keeps a thread alive. However she is a mid-level Sourcing Lead (IT category) contracted through IBM, not a power sponsor, and she has not delivered the demo dates or escalated to the head of procurement she named. Her 8 Jun 2026 note ('When the project will be continued I will contact you') is a cooling, hold-the-line signal rather than active advocacy. The move is to give her a quantified business case as air cover and convert her into a sponsored channel to the head of procurement rather than relying on her alone."}, "competition": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Avoma discovery call 18 Jul 2025 (Zsofia Ambrus-Csetreki)", "SF Next_Step__c"], "narrative": "The principal competitive dynamic is the incumbent Coupa plus a strong 'do nothing / re-optimise Coupa' risk. On 18 Jul 2025 Zsofia confirmed Coupa is already in place for requisitions, orders and reporting but not used for sourcing because it was under-configured, and stressed the RFP's purpose is 'not to challenge Coupa' for P2P, only to add sourcing; Honda has not decided whether to keep Coupa. The Next Step note also records a 'bias towards Coupa' and that Deloitte has early engagement pushing an S2P+CLM agenda and to remove SAP, with confirmed internal politics, a system-integrator influence that could steer the buyer toward a Coupa-centric outcome. Our wedge is embedded sourcing automation, autonomous negotiation (Merlin / Agentic AI), and one integrated platform that dovetails with Coupa reporting and the intake form."}, "identify_pain": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Avoma discovery call 18 Jul 2025 (Zsofia Ambrus-Csetreki)"], "narrative": "Pain is clearly articulated and owned by the sourcing team. On 18 Jul 2025 Zsofia described sourcing running entirely manually: RFPs sent by email because suppliers cannot open Coupa links, proposals collected on SharePoint, and evaluations scored live in meetings on a complex Excel scorecard, with new Coupa access required each time an evaluator is added. Coupa was bought but under-configured ('we did not put enough energy into the configuration customization'), so it is not used for sourcing at all. The pain owner is Zsofia and the Budapest sourcing team supporting indirect sourcing across 18 European countries. This is confirmed, vivid operational pain; what is missing is the financial impact and an executive who feels it acutely enough to unblock the project."}, "paper_process": {"status": "gap", "sources": ["Avoma discovery call 18 Jul 2025 (Zsofia Ambrus-Csetreki)"], "narrative": "No contracting mechanics have been engaged. On 18 Jul 2025 Zsofia noted an NDA had been shared and acknowledged 'contracting sometimes takes weeks', which is why she originally targeted a year-end 2025 signature, but no MSA, SOW, legal, procurement-channel or InfoSec activity has followed in the ~11.7 months since, and no contract-expiration forcing function is on record. Honda's outsourcing of procurement to IBM adds an operating-model layer to any future paper process. What would create visibility is confirmation of the RFP release and the procurement/legal path once the project restarts."}, "economic_buyer": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Avoma discovery call 18 Jul 2025 (Zsofia Ambrus-Csetreki)", "SF OpportunityContactRole"], "narrative": "The budget authority is named by role but never engaged. On 18 Jul 2025 Zsofia named the head of procurement (UK) as her main stakeholder and the person who runs volume reports, plus the head of finance (UK) as a co-stakeholder, and said 'we have a project' with budget but 'we do not know what to expect'. Neither the head of procurement nor the head of finance is